# ELMO — Networked Intelligence of JASON Agents

## Introduction
An LLM agent system on Emacs, which offers unique characteristics:
- Full CUI operations with rich GUI
- Interfaces for hacking tools seasoned by history
- Self-evolving potentials inherited from Emacs and Elisp

Here, we reintroduce Emacs — born in MIT's AI Lab in 1970s — as a catalyst for AI agents.

## Quick Start
```bash
git clone https://github.com/user/ELMO.git ~/.emacs.d/ELMO
```

## Apptainer

``` bash
apptainer build \
    --sandbox \
    --fakeroot \
    ./.apptainer/elmo/elmo.sandbox \
    ./.apptainer/elmo/elmo.def \
    2>&1 | tee ./.apptainer/elmo/elmo.sandbox.log
    
apptainer shell \
    --fakeroot \
    --writable \
    ./.apptainer/elmo/elmo.sandbox
```

## Usage

``` bash
./run.sh
```

